This paper deals with cyber-security and reinforcement learning, which are both relevant to the sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper proposes a reinforcement learning approach, which suggests that it could also belong to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses game theory and the development of a competitive baseline, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-category of cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Finally, the paper discusses the retraining of the defender with episodes from an attacker policy, which suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of cs.SE (Software Engineering).
